history.content: Normally I wouldn't recommend a semester like this. However, you've already gotten an A in Stat 134, which does mean the probability portion will be significantly easier; that being said, CS70 has a pretty high workload (I've heard Stat 133 isn't too bad, and Math 54 isn't either), so while it might be doable, it will still be a very high workload overall.

children.subject: This seems very doable. Stat 133 is very easy for someone with a programming background, and 53/16A should give you enough background to do 54 fairly easily. That leaves you with plenty of time to work on 70 and the other class.

history.content: Highly recommend against taking 4 techs at once if at all possible.

I'm a rising sophomore, intending to declare both LSCS and Stats at the end of next semester. In the fall, would it be too heavy if I took Math 54, DATA C100, CS 70, and Stat 133? 

I'm currently signed up for the first two, and will need to add the latter two during Phase II/Adjustment. If I end up adding both, which should I Phase II?

For reference, I have gotten A's in 61AB and Stat 134, and A-'s in EE16A and Math 53. (also Data 8, but grade unknown as of posting this. Probably an A of some sort.)

Thanks for your thoughts!
history.subject: 4 Techs Schedule - Thoughts?
